## Task 1: Relation Extraction with Classification Head

### Approach
- **Base Model:** Qwen/Qwen2.5-1.5B (frozen) with LoRA adapters (r=16, О±=32)
- **Entity Marking:** Special tokens `[EM1]/[/EM1]` and `[EM2]/[/EM2]` inserted 
  around entity spans in the sentence
- **Pooling Strategy:** Mean pooling over entity token positions (entity-aware 
  pooling) for both E1 and E2 separately, then concatenated в†’ `[e1; e2]` of 
  size `2 Г— hidden_size` fed to linear classifier
- **Training Data:** English NYT-10 + Hindi (200) + Kannada (200), with Indic 
  labels mapped back to English
- **Class Imbalance:** Inverse frequency class weights in CrossEntropyLoss
- **Per-Language Max Lengths:** English=142, Hindi=400, Kannada=512 tokens
- **Per-Language Batch Sizes:** English=16, Hindi=8, Kannada=4
- **Round-Robin Training:** Separate DataLoader per language, batches interleaved 
  in round-robin to avoid cross-language padding waste
- **Optimizer:** AdamW (lr=1e-4, weight_decay=0.01) + CosineAnnealingLR
- **Epochs:** 5, Best checkpoint saved by Macro-F1 on English validation set

### Results
| Language | Micro-F1 | Macro-F1 |
|---|---|---|
| English | 0.8399 | 0.8674 |
| Hindi | 0.8203 | 0.8720 |
| Kannada | 0.8132 |  0.8718 |

